David S. Gellman  Managing Director, FdG Associates LPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships59--
Background

		Mr. David S. Gellman serves as the Managing Director of FdG Associates LP. Mr. Gellman co-founded FdG in 1995. Mr. Gellman serves as the Managing Director of FdG Capital Partners II LP and FdG Capital Partners LLC. He served as Managing Director of AEA Investors Inc. He has 11 years of private equity experience and was responsible for successful investments in a variety of industries from 1988 to 1995 and at the Trump Group's private equity division. In addition to his ... investment activities at AEA, he served as the Chief Executive Officer and the Chief Financial Officer of several portfolio companies. Previously, Mr. Gellman had been with AEA for seven years and Trump Group’s private equity division for four years. Mr. Gellman began his business career in acquisition finance at Bankers Trust Company, where he was one of the Co-Founders of the New York Leveraged Finance Group. He serves as an Independent Director of Limbach Holdings, Inc. since July 20, 2016. He serves on the Boards of Directors/Managers of USA Bouquet and Infrastructure and Industrial Constructors USA. He served as a Director of The Hercules Tire & Rubber Company; Seabrook International, LLC; DentaQuest Ventures, Inc., and ReTrans. Previously, Mr. Gellman served as a Director of A&R Logistics, Inc.; SiteOne Landscape Supply, Inc. River Ranch Fresh Foods, LLC; DentaQuest, Inc.; Implus Corporation, Vitamin Shoppe Industries Inc.; McGinnis Farms Inc.; Industrial Controls Distributors LLC; Golf Galaxy, LLC (Former Name: Golf Galaxy, Inc.); and CBP Resources, Inc. He served as a Director of VitaminShoppe.com, Inc., since May 1999. He served as a Board Member of Implus Footcare, LLC; North American Training Services Inc.; and Sunrise Windows Ltd. Mr. Gellman holds an M.M. degree from the Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University and an A.B. in Neuropsychology from Cornell University.Read Full Background




