Home  HomeThe PressCompanies RepresentedTerritory CoverageOur Mission StatementContact Us      ​​​​Gellman Associates LLC2511 Fire Rd. Unit A-1Egg Harbor Twp, NJ 08234Phones: 800-345-1046               609-365-1444Fax:       609-277-7739gellmankak@aol.comDavid Gellman – Principald.gellm@att.netCell: 484-433-2064   GELLMAN ASSOCIATES is a specialized Manufacturer’s Representative in food products and food service equipment providing in-depth representation to Convenience Stores, Vending, Office Coffee Service and Mobile Caterers covering New Jersey, Pennsylvania, Delaware, Maryland and Virginia. Gellman Associates furnishes distributor support, along with direct sales, for the manufacturers we represent.  We take an active role in all regional and national trade associations.   DAVID GELLMAN has been actively involved in the vending industry since 1968.  He was the founding President of the National Vend Brokers Association in 1977 and served as President of the Association again in 1997 and 1998.   In 1995 David won the “Supplier of the Year” award from the Keystone Coffee Association.  He was inducted into the National Beverage Products Association “Hall of Fame” in 1997.  David has served on the Broker Advisory Boards for many of the companies we represent. He has also served on the VSA Broker Advisory Board. David previously served  on the Board of Directors for the Keystone Coffee Association. David completed a two- year term as President of the Pennsylvania Automatic Merchandising Council (now name changed to Tri-State Automatic Merchandising Council). He also served on NAMA’s Broker Advisory Board.  At the request of NAMA, David was a guest lecturer in October of 2000 at Michigan State University’s School of Hospitality.  David was also named Allied Member of the Year-Vending of the National Automatic Merchandising Association (NAMA) for 2004.  David was named Program Chairman for NAMA’s first powerful new Coffee Summit held in Philadelphia in February 2008. The event was a tremendous success with over 400 attendees.David was named 2008 Broker of the Year by Automatic Merchandiser Magazine David directly manages the vend distributors in the metropolitan Philadelphia market and oversees the distributors in Maryland, Virginia, Northern New Jersey, Metropolitan New York and Long Island. In addition to having customer responsibility he also oversees all administrative activities.  ​Gellman Associates  takes pride in their ability to develop lines and maximize sales. Below is a sampling of our many achievement awards:                                                                                                                                                       2016                                                    NAMA - inducted to the Coffee Hall of Fame                                                                                  2010                                                         Everpure- 2009 Broker of the Year                                                                Coffee and Office Water                                                     Everpure 2009 One Million Dollar Club                                                                                  2009                                               Automatic Merchandiser Broker of the Year                                                                                  2008                                                       Chairman of NAMA Coffee Summit                                                                                  2004                                                National Automatic Merchandising Association                                                       Allied Member of the Year – Vending                                                                                  2002                                                          White Castle Broker of the Year                                              